	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Louis</placeName>&#44; <date>June 6&#44; 1862</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44; <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#44;</p>
				<p>Honored Sir&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Along with the hope that my letter may find you in the best<lb/> of health&#44; I am sending you herewith &#36;15. for books sold.  Have the good&#45;<lb/>ness to send me 3 or 4 dozen of the Hebrew readers.  Send it by express.<lb/>  It has been impossible for me&#44; until now&#44; to collect anything either for<lb/> your paper or for that of <persName>Wise</persName> or <persName>Isaacs</persName>.  Times are very bad here.<lb/>  People barely have enough for necessities&#44; so bad is business.  There is<lb/> no news.  That is why I want to close with the question whether you have<lb/> received my &#36;15.  As soon as times change I shall collect once more.  You<lb/> have my last letter with the &#36;15. which has remained unanswered now for<lb/> a long time.  In my German congregation I have peace&#44; thank God&#44; and hope<lb/> that the situation will remain so.  The beginning has been made&#44; and the<lb/> firm of <persName>Marx and Schoen</persName> observe the <date>Sabbath</date> and their business is complete&#45;<lb/>ly closed.  Also 2 baker members of my community now observe the <date>Sabbath</date>.<lb/>  In time I hope that others will do so.  On <date>Shabuoth</date>&#44; the son of <persName>L. R. Straus</persName><lb/> became Bar&#45;Mitzvah&#44; as well as 3 other boys who did me honor&#44; since&#44; as<lb/> you know&#44; my congregation is purely German&#44; everything was conducted in<lb/> the German language&#44; except for the religious questions which I taught<lb/> out of your valuable book.  It is possible that <persName>Mr. Straus</persName> will write to<lb/> you about it.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Wishing you constant health&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Your devoted</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">M. Kuttner</persName></p>
		</body>
